summary: 4,000-6,000 job cuts to increase productivity through AI, targeting $1B savings by FY2028: HP announced November 2025 it would reduce global headcount by 4,000-6,000 employees as part of an initiative to increase productivity using AI, targeting $1B in savings by fiscal year 2028.
